The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Wednesday, August 03, 2005 

 BRIEFS

 Suri, Aug. 2: Seven people were killed around noon when a speeding truck hit a private bus in the Mohammad Bazar area of Birbhum.

 The bus from Suri was headed for Muraroi, about 100 km away. Among the dead Prasanta Ghosh, 45, Prabir Mukherjee, 45, Abdul Samad, 50, and Rabi Sheikh, 30, the bus driver, have been identified. The driver of the truck died as well. Fourteen passengers had to be admitted to Suri Sadar Hospital. 

 Chinsurah: Four officials of a steel unit in the UK were injured on Monday night when their car hit construction equipment on the roadside while trying to avoid a motorcycle on Durgapur Expressway. Police said A. Anderson, P. Thomas, F. Erricson and Lily Jones, who went to Jamuria near Asansol to see the site of a proposed plant, met with the accident at Chanditala in Hooghly, 30 km from Calcutta.




